	"briefing.scenario_0": [
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Your First Loading Shift[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]HOW IT WORKS IN REAL LIFE[/color][/font_size]\n\nEvery morning the shift captain assigns each operator their loadings for the day. It is good practice to be in the office 15 minutes before your loading starts, so you have time to prepare your paperwork before heading to the dock — that is why every scenario in this training begins the same way.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]1. OFFICE[/b][/color]\nYou go to the office and pick up three things from the desk: the [b]CMR[/b] (transport document that goes with the driver), the [b]Loading Sheet[/b] (your operational counting record), and the [b]seal[/b] (physical lock for the trailer doors). You fill in what you already know — store name, seal number, dock number — on both the CMR and the Loading Sheet.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]2. DOCK & AS400[/b][/color]\nYou go to your dock and open it (raise the leveler). Then you open the AS400 terminal and register the expedition: enter the store destination code and the seal number. The AS400 gives you an expedition number — you write that on your Loading Sheet and your CMR.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]3. CHECK THE RAQ[/b][/color]\nPress F13 in the AS400 to open the RAQ — the digital list of pallets assigned to your truck. Check that you have the correct number of Click & Collect pallets on the dock floor. If any are missing, call the departments responsible (B2C, Bikes) [b]before[/b] you start loading.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]4. LOAD THE TRUCK[/b][/color]\nLoad in the correct sequence: [b]Service Center → Bikes → Bulky → Mecha → Click & Collect[/b]. C&C always goes last, nearest to the trailer doors.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]5. PAPERWORK & AS400 CONFIRM[/b][/color]\nAfter everything is inside the truck, fill in the remaining fields on your CMR and Loading Sheet (counts, colli, EUR pallets, etc.). Go back to the AS400 and press F10 to confirm. The final AS400 screen shows the total weight and volume — write those on your CMR.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]6. CLOSE OUT[/b][/color]\nBack in the office, you transfer the Loading Sheet information to the Loading Plan board. You give the CMR to the driver, who fills in the carrier section and returns the first page to you. You staple it on top of the Loading Sheet and put it in the office locker. Then you go outside with the driver, seal the truck together, and the loading is done.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]This tutorial will guide you through each step with on-screen instructions.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Je Eerste Laadbeurt[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]HOE HET IN HET ECHT WERKT[/color][/font_size]\n\nElke ochtend wijst de ploegcaptain elke operator zijn ladingen toe voor die dag. Het is goed gebruik om 15 minuten voor je lading begint in het kantoor te zijn, zodat je tijd hebt om je papierwerk voor te bereiden — daarom begint elk scenario in deze training op dezelfde manier.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]1. OFFICE[/b][/color]\nJe gaat naar het kantoor en pakt drie dingen van het bureau: de [b]CMR[/b] (transportdocument dat meegaat met de chauffeur), het [b]Laadblad[/b] (je operationele telformulier) en de [b]seal[/b] (fysiek slot voor de trailerdeuren). Je vult in wat je al weet — winkelnaam, sealnummer, doknummer — op zowel de CMR als het Laadblad.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]2. DOK & AS400[/b][/color]\nJe gaat naar je dok en opent het (brug omhoog). Dan open je de AS400-terminal en registreer je de expeditie: voer de winkelbestemmingscode en het sealnummer in. De AS400 geeft je een expeditienummer — dat schrijf je op je Laadblad en je CMR.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]3. RAQ CONTROLEREN[/b][/color]\nDruk op F13 in de AS400 om de RAQ te openen — de digitale lijst met pallets toegewezen aan jouw vrachtwagen. Controleer of je het juiste aantal Click & Collect pallets op de dokvloer hebt. Als er ontbreken, bel je de verantwoordelijke afdelingen (B2C, Bikes) [b]voordat[/b] je begint met laden.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]4. VRACHTWAGEN LADEN[/b][/color]\nLaad in de juiste volgorde: [b]Service Center → Bikes → Bulky → Mecha → Click & Collect[/b]. C&C gaat altijd als laatste, het dichtst bij de trailerdeuren.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]5. PAPIERWERK & AS400 BEVESTIGEN[/b][/color]\nNadat alles in de vrachtwagen staat, vul je de resterende velden in op je CMR en Laadblad (aantallen, colli, EUR-pallets, enz.). Ga terug naar de AS400 en druk op F10 om te bevestigen. Het laatste AS400-scherm toont het totaalgewicht en volume — schrijf die op je CMR.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]6. AFSLUITEN[/b][/color]\nTerug op kantoor zet je de Laadblad-informatie over naar het Laadplanbord. Je geeft de CMR aan de chauffeur, die het vervoerdersgedeelte invult en de eerste pagina aan jou teruggeeft. Je niet die bovenop het Laadblad en legt het in het kantoorkastje. Dan ga je met de chauffeur naar buiten, verzegelen jullie samen de vrachtwagen, en de lading is klaar.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Deze zelfstudie begeleidt je stap voor stap met instructies op het scherm.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Votre Premier Chargement[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]COMMENT ÇA SE PASSE EN VRAI[/color][/font_size]\n\nChaque matin, le capitaine d'équipe attribue les chargements à chaque opérateur. Il est recommandé d'être au bureau 15 minutes avant votre chargement pour préparer vos documents — c'est pourquoi chaque scénario commence ainsi.\n\nVous passez par: [b]Bureau[/b] (prendre CMR, feuille de chargement, scellé) → [b]Quai & AS400[/b] (ouvrir le quai, enregistrer l'expédition) → [b]Vérifier le RAQ[/b] (F13, contrôler C&C) → [b]Charger[/b] (SC → Bikes → Bulky → Mecha → C&C) → [b]Paperasse & Confirmer AS400[/b] (F10, poids/volume) → [b]Clôturer[/b] (plan de chargement, CMR au chauffeur, sceller).\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Ce tutoriel vous guidera étape par étape.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]O Seu Primeiro Carregamento[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]COMO FUNCIONA NA VIDA REAL[/color][/font_size]\n\nTodas as manhãs, o capitão de turno atribui carregamentos a cada operador. É boa prática estar no escritório 15 minutos antes do carregamento para preparar os documentos — por isso cada cenário começa da mesma forma.\n\nO fluxo: [b]Escritório[/b] (pegar CMR, folha de carga, selo) → [b]Cais & AS400[/b] (abrir cais, registar expedição) → [b]Verificar RAQ[/b] (F13, conferir C&C) → [b]Carregar[/b] (SC → Bikes → Bulky → Mecha → C&C) → [b]Papelada & Confirmar AS400[/b] (F10, peso/volume) → [b]Fechar[/b] (plano de carga, CMR ao motorista, selar).\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Este tutorial guiá-lo-á passo a passo.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Tu Primera Carga[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]CÓMO FUNCIONA EN LA VIDA REAL[/color][/font_size]\n\nCada mañana, el capitán de turno asigna las cargas. Es buena práctica estar en la oficina 15 minutos antes de tu carga para preparar los documentos — por eso cada escenario comienza igual.\n\nEl flujo: [b]Oficina[/b] (recoger CMR, hoja de carga, sello) → [b]Muelle & AS400[/b] (abrir muelle, registrar expedición) → [b]Verificar RAQ[/b] (F13, comprobar C&C) → [b]Cargar[/b] (SC → Bikes → Bulky → Mecha → C&C) → [b]Papeleo & Confirmar AS400[/b] (F10, peso/volumen) → [b]Cerrar[/b] (plan de carga, CMR al conductor, sellar).\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Este tutorial te guiará paso a paso.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Il Tuo Primo Caricamento[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]COME FUNZIONA NELLA VITA REALE[/color][/font_size]\n\nOgni mattina il capitano di turno assegna i caricamenti. È buona pratica essere in ufficio 15 minuti prima del caricamento per preparare i documenti — per questo ogni scenario inizia allo stesso modo.\n\nIl flusso: [b]Ufficio[/b] (prendere CMR, foglio di carico, sigillo) → [b]Banchina & AS400[/b] (aprire banchina, registrare spedizione) → [b]Verificare RAQ[/b] (F13, controllare C&C) → [b]Caricare[/b] (SC → Bikes → Bulky → Mecha → C&C) → [b]Documenti & Confermare AS400[/b] (F10, peso/volume) → [b]Chiudere[/b] (piano di carico, CMR all'autista, sigillare).\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Questo tutorial ti guiderà passo dopo passo.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Vaš Prvi Utovar[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]KAKO TO FUNKCIONIRA U STVARNOM ŽIVOTU[/color][/font_size]\n\nSvako jutro kapetan smjene dodjeljuje utovare. Dobra je praksa biti u uredu 15 minuta prije utovara kako biste pripremili dokumente — zato svaki scenarij počinje na isti način.\n\nTok: [b]Ured[/b] (uzeti CMR, list utovara, plombu) → [b]Dok & AS400[/b] (otvoriti dok, registrirati otpremu) → [b]Provjeriti RAQ[/b] (F13, kontrolirati C&C) → [b]Utovariti[/b] (SC → Bikes → Bulky → Mecha → C&C) → [b]Dokumenti & Potvrditi AS400[/b] (F10, težina/volumen) → [b]Zatvoriti[/b] (plan utovara, CMR vozaču, zapečatiti).\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Ovaj vodič će vas provesti korak po korak.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Twój Pierwszy Załadunek[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]JAK TO WYGLĄDA W RZECZYWISTOŚCI[/color][/font_size]\n\nKażdego ranka kapitan zmiany przydziela załadunki. Dobrą praktyką jest być w biurze 15 minut przed załadunkiem, aby przygotować dokumenty — dlatego każdy scenariusz zaczyna się w ten sam sposób.\n\nPrzebieg: [b]Biuro[/b] (zabrać CMR, arkusz załadunkowy, plombę) → [b]Dok & AS400[/b] (otworzyć dok, zarejestrować ekspedycję) → [b]Sprawdzić RAQ[/b] (F13, skontrolować C&C) → [b]Załadować[/b] (SC → Bikes → Bulky → Mecha → C&C) → [b]Dokumenty & Potwierdzić AS400[/b] (F10, waga/objętość) → [b]Zamknąć[/b] (plan załadunku, CMR kierowcy, zaplombować).\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Ten samouczek poprowadzi Cię krok po kroku.[/color]",
	],
	"briefing.scenario_1": [
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Standard Loading[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]WHAT TO EXPECT[/color][/font_size]\n\nYou have completed the tutorial — now do it on your own. This is a standard single-store loading with no surprises.\n\nEverything works the same as the tutorial, but without the step-by-step guidance. You are expected to remember the correct flow: Office → Dock → AS400 → RAQ check → Load → Paperwork → Confirm → Seal.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]What's new:[/b][/color]\n\n• You may receive [b]phone calls[/b] from departments during your shift — answer them and act accordingly.\n• New [b]SOP articles[/b] are unlocked covering CMR rules, Loading Sheet procedures, dock line protocols, and quality standards. Use the SOP button if you need a refresher.\n• No hand-holding — mistakes will be scored.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Good luck, operator.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Standaard Laden[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]WAT TE VERWACHTEN[/color][/font_size]\n\nJe hebt de zelfstudie afgerond — nu doe je het zelf. Dit is een standaard lading voor één winkel zonder verrassingen.\n\nAlles werkt hetzelfde als de zelfstudie, maar zonder stapsgewijze begeleiding. Je wordt verwacht de juiste flow te onthouden: Office → Dok → AS400 → RAQ check → Laden → Papierwerk → Bevestigen → Verzegelen.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]Wat is nieuw:[/b][/color]\n\n• Je kunt [b]telefoontjes[/b] krijgen van afdelingen tijdens je dienst — beantwoord ze en handel ernaar.\n• Nieuwe [b]SOP-artikelen[/b] zijn ontgrendeld over CMR-regels, Laadblad-procedures, doklijnen en kwaliteitsstandaarden.\n• Geen begeleiding — fouten worden gescoord.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Succes, operator.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Chargement Standard[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]À QUOI S'ATTENDRE[/color][/font_size]\n\nVous avez terminé le tutoriel — maintenant, faites-le seul. Chargement standard pour un seul magasin, sans surprises. Vous pourriez recevoir des appels téléphoniques. De nouveaux articles SOP sont débloqués.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Bonne chance, opérateur.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Carregamento Padrão[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]O QUE ESPERAR[/color][/font_size]\n\nCompletou o tutorial — agora faça sozinho. Carregamento padrão para uma loja, sem surpresas. Pode receber telefonemas. Novos artigos SOP desbloqueados.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Boa sorte, operador.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Carga Estándar[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]QUÉ ESPERAR[/color][/font_size]\n\nHa completado el tutorial — ahora hágalo solo. Carga estándar para una tienda, sin sorpresas. Puede recibir llamadas telefónicas. Nuevos artículos SOP desbloqueados.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Buena suerte, operador.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Caricamento Standard[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]COSA ASPETTARSI[/color][/font_size]\n\nHai completato il tutorial — ora fallo da solo. Caricamento standard per un singolo negozio, senza sorprese. Potresti ricevere telefonate. Nuovi articoli SOP sbloccati.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Buona fortuna, operatore.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Standardno Utovarivanje[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]ŠTO OČEKIVATI[/color][/font_size]\n\nZavršili ste vodič — sada to učinite sami. Standardni utovar za jednu trgovinu, bez iznenađenja. Možete primiti telefonske pozive. Novi SOP članci su otključani.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Sretno, operateru.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Standardowy Załadunek[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]CZEGO SIĘ SPODZIEWAĆ[/color][/font_size]\n\nUkończyłeś samouczek — teraz zrób to sam. Standardowy załadunek dla jednego sklepu, bez niespodzianek. Możesz otrzymać telefony. Nowe artykuły SOP odblokowane.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Powodzenia, operatorze.[/color]",
	],
	"briefing.scenario_2": [
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Priority Loading[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]WHAT TO EXPECT[/color][/font_size]\n\nHigh-volume day. More pallets have arrived than your truck can physically hold. You must decide what to load and what to leave behind.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]What's new:[/b][/color]\n\n• [b]Promise Dates[/b] now matter. Each pallet has a delivery promise:\n  — [color=#e74c3c][b]D-[/b][/color] = overdue (highest priority, must go)\n  — [b]D[/b] = due today (high priority)\n  — [color=#3498db]D+[/color] = due tomorrow (can wait if needed)\n\n• The [b]captain or supervisor may call[/b] you with instructions about which pallets to prioritise.\n\n• Everything else follows the standard process — Office → AS400 → RAQ → Load → Paperwork — but the pressure is on your [b]sequencing decisions[/b].\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]In real life, leaving behind D- pallets means a store misses its delivery promise to a customer. Choose wisely.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Prioriteit Laden[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]WAT TE VERWACHTEN[/color][/font_size]\n\nDrukke dag. Er zijn meer pallets dan je vrachtwagen kan bevatten. Je moet beslissen wat je laadt en wat je achterlaat.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]Wat is nieuw:[/b][/color]\n\n• [b]Leverdata[/b] zijn nu belangrijk:\n  — [color=#e74c3c][b]D-[/b][/color] = achterstallig (hoogste prioriteit, moet mee)\n  — [b]D[/b] = vandaag (hoge prioriteit)\n  — [color=#3498db]D+[/color] = morgen (kan wachten indien nodig)\n\n• De [b]captain of supervisor kan bellen[/b] met instructies over welke pallets prioriteit krijgen.\n\n• De rest volgt het standaardproces, maar de druk ligt op je [b]keuzes in volgorde[/b].\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]In het echt betekent D- pallets achterlaten dat een winkel zijn leverbelofte aan de klant breekt. Kies verstandig.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Chargement Prioritaire[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]À QUOI S'ATTENDRE[/color][/font_size]\n\nJournée à fort volume. Plus de palettes que le camion ne peut contenir. Vous devez décider quoi charger selon les dates de promesse: D- (en retard), D (aujourd'hui), D+ (demain). Le capitaine peut appeler avec des instructions.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Laisser des palettes D- = promesse client brisée.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Carregamento Prioritário[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]O QUE ESPERAR[/color][/font_size]\n\nDia de alto volume. Mais paletes do que o camião comporta. Decida o que carregar com base nas datas de promessa: D- (atrasado), D (hoje), D+ (amanhã). O capitão pode ligar com instruções.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Deixar paletes D- = promessa ao cliente quebrada.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Carga Prioritaria[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]QUÉ ESPERAR[/color][/font_size]\n\nDía de alto volumen. Más palés de los que caben. Decida qué cargar según fechas de promesa: D- (atrasado), D (hoy), D+ (mañana). El capitán puede llamar con instrucciones.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Dejar palés D- = promesa al cliente rota.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Caricamento Prioritario[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]COSA ASPETTARSI[/color][/font_size]\n\nGiornata ad alto volume. Più pallet di quanti ne entrano. Decidi cosa caricare in base alle date di promessa: D- (in ritardo), D (oggi), D+ (domani). Il capitano potrebbe chiamare.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Lasciare pallet D- = promessa al cliente infranta.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Prioritetni Utovar[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]ŠTO OČEKIVATI[/color][/font_size]\n\nDan visokog volumena. Više paleta nego što kamion može primiti. Odlučite na temelju datuma isporuke: D- (kasni), D (danas), D+ (sutra). Kapetan može nazvati s uputama.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Ostaviti D- palete = prekršena obećanja kupcu.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Załadunek Priorytetowy[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]CZEGO SIĘ SPODZIEWAĆ[/color][/font_size]\n\nDzień dużego wolumenu. Więcej palet niż zmieści ciężarówka. Zdecyduj co załadować według dat obietnic: D- (zaległe), D (dziś), D+ (jutro). Kapitan może zadzwonić z instrukcjami.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Zostawienie palet D- = złamana obietnica dla klienta.[/color]",
	],
	"briefing.scenario_3": [
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Co-Loading[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]WHAT TO EXPECT[/color][/font_size]\n\nTwo stores share one truck — this is called a co-loading (CO). The truck is split: one store's pallets go deep inside (Sequence 1), the other store's pallets go near the doors (Sequence 2). The first store on the delivery route gets unloaded first, so its goods must be accessible.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]What's new:[/b][/color]\n\n• [b]Two sets of paperwork[/b] — one Loading Sheet and one CMR per store, plus two seals (one per store).\n• In the [b]AS400[/b], you register each store on a separate tab.\n• The [b]Loading Plan board[/b] shows which store is Seq.1 and which is Seq.2.\n• [b]Never mix pallets[/b] between the two destinations — this is the most common and most serious mistake in co-loading.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]In real life, mixing pallets in a CO means the wrong store receives someone else's goods. It creates returns, delays, and unhappy customers.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Co-Laden[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]WAT TE VERWACHTEN[/color][/font_size]\n\nTwee winkels delen één vrachtwagen — dit heet een co-lading (CO). De vrachtwagen wordt gesplitst: de pallets van de ene winkel gaan diep erin (Sequentie 1), die van de andere bij de deuren (Sequentie 2). De eerste winkel op de leverroute wordt eerst gelost, dus die goederen moeten bereikbaar zijn.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]Wat is nieuw:[/b][/color]\n\n• [b]Twee sets papierwerk[/b] — één Laadblad en één CMR per winkel, plus twee seals.\n• In de [b]AS400[/b] registreer je elke winkel op een apart tabblad.\n• Het [b]Laadplanbord[/b] toont welke winkel Seq.1 is en welke Seq.2.\n• [b]Meng nooit pallets[/b] tussen de twee bestemmingen — dit is de meest voorkomende en ernstigste fout bij co-laden.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]In het echt betekent pallets mengen bij een CO dat de verkeerde winkel andermans goederen ontvangt. Dat veroorzaakt retouren, vertragingen en ontevreden klanten.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Co-Chargement[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]À QUOI S'ATTENDRE[/color][/font_size]\n\nDeux magasins partagent un camion (CO). Séquence 1 au fond, Séquence 2 près des portes. Deux jeux de documents (CMR + feuille de chargement par magasin), deux scellés. Ne mélangez jamais les palettes entre destinations.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Mélanger les palettes = le mauvais magasin reçoit les mauvais produits.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Co-Carregamento[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]O QUE ESPERAR[/color][/font_size]\n\nDuas lojas partilham um camião (CO). Sequência 1 ao fundo, Sequência 2 perto das portas. Dois conjuntos de documentos (CMR + folha de carga por loja), dois selos. Nunca misture paletes entre destinos.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Misturar paletes = loja errada recebe produtos errados.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Co-Carga[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]QUÉ ESPERAR[/color][/font_size]\n\nDos tiendas comparten un camión (CO). Secuencia 1 al fondo, Secuencia 2 cerca de las puertas. Dos juegos de documentos (CMR + hoja de carga por tienda), dos sellos. Nunca mezcle palés entre destinos.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Mezclar palés = la tienda equivocada recibe productos equivocados.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Co-Caricamento[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]COSA ASPETTARSI[/color][/font_size]\n\nDue negozi condividono un camion (CO). Sequenza 1 in fondo, Sequenza 2 vicino alle porte. Due set di documenti (CMR + foglio di carico per negozio), due sigilli. Non mescolare mai pallet tra destinazioni.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Mescolare pallet = il negozio sbagliato riceve i prodotti sbagliati.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Co-Utovar[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]ŠTO OČEKIVATI[/color][/font_size]\n\nDvije trgovine dijele jedan kamion (CO). Sekvencija 1 dublje, Sekvencija 2 blizu vrata. Dva kompleta dokumenata (CMR + list utovara po trgovini), dvije plombe. Nikad ne miješajte palete.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Miješanje paleta = kriva trgovina prima krive proizvode.[/color]",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Co-Załadunek[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]CZEGO SIĘ SPODZIEWAĆ[/color][/font_size]\n\nDwa sklepy dzielą jedną ciężarówkę (CO). Sekwencja 1 głębiej, Sekwencja 2 bliżej drzwi. Dwa komplety dokumentów (CMR + arkusz załadunkowy na sklep), dwie plomby. Nigdy nie mieszaj palet.\n\n[color=#a0a4aa]Mieszanie palet = zły sklep otrzymuje złe produkty.[/color]",
	],
	"briefing.scenario_4": [
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Free Play — Sandbox[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]EXPLORE AT YOUR OWN PACE[/color][/font_size]\n\nThis is an open sandbox with no scoring and no time pressure. The dock is yours.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]What you can do:[/b][/color]\n\n• Load and unload pallets freely — experiment with sequence.\n• Navigate the AS400 — try every screen, every F-key.\n• Fill out the Loading Sheet and CMR — practice the fields.\n• Open the dock, call departments, check transit and ADR.\n• Make as many deliberate mistakes as you want — nothing is graded.\n\nWhen you are done, press [b]Seal Truck[/b] to return to the portal. No debrief will be shown.",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Vrij Spelen — Sandbox[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]VERKEN OP JE EIGEN TEMPO[/color][/font_size]\n\nDit is een open sandbox zonder score en zonder tijdsdruk. Het dok is van jou.\n\n[color=#f1c40f][b]Wat je kunt doen:[/b][/color]\n\n• Pallets laden en lossen — experimenteer met de volgorde.\n• Navigeer door de AS400 — probeer elk scherm, elke F-toets.\n• Vul het Laadblad en de CMR in — oefen de velden.\n• Open het dok, bel afdelingen, controleer transit en ADR.\n• Maak zo veel bewuste fouten als je wilt — er wordt niets beoordeeld.\n\nAls je klaar bent, druk op [b]Seal Truck[/b] om terug te gaan naar het portaal. Er wordt geen debriefing getoond.",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Jeu Libre — Bac à sable[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]EXPLOREZ À VOTRE RYTHME[/color][/font_size]\n\nUn bac à sable ouvert sans score ni pression de temps. Le quai est à vous.\n\nChargez, naviguez dans l'AS400, remplissez les documents. Faites des erreurs volontaires — rien n'est noté. Appuyez sur [b]Sceller le camion[/b] pour revenir au portail.",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Jogo Livre — Sandbox[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]EXPLORE AO SEU RITMO[/color][/font_size]\n\nUm sandbox aberto sem pontuação nem pressão de tempo. O cais é seu.\n\nCarregue, navegue no AS400, preencha os documentos. Faça erros deliberados — nada é avaliado. Pressione [b]Selar Camião[/b] para voltar ao portal.",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Juego Libre — Sandbox[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]EXPLORA A TU RITMO[/color][/font_size]\n\nUn sandbox abierto sin puntuación ni presión de tiempo. El muelle es tuyo.\n\nCarga, navega por el AS400, rellena los documentos. Comete errores deliberados — nada se califica. Pulsa [b]Sellar Camión[/b] para volver al portal.",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Gioco Libero — Sandbox[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]ESPLORA AL TUO RITMO[/color][/font_size]\n\nUn sandbox aperto senza punteggio né pressione di tempo. La banchina è tua.\n\nCarica, naviga nell'AS400, compila i documenti. Fai errori deliberati — nulla viene valutato. Premi [b]Sigilla Camion[/b] per tornare al portale.",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Slobodna Igra — Sandbox[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]ISTRAŽUJTE VLASTITIM TEMPOM[/color][/font_size]\n\nOtvoreni sandbox bez bodovanja i vremenskog pritiska. Dok je vaš.\n\nUtovarajte, navigirajte AS400, popunite dokumente. Radite namjerne greške — ništa se ne ocjenjuje. Pritisnite [b]Zapečati kamion[/b] za povratak na portal.",
		"[font_size=22][color=#0082c3][b]Gra Swobodna — Sandbox[/b][/color][/font_size]\n\n[font_size=14][color=#a0a4aa]EKSPLORUJ WE WŁASNYM TEMPIE[/color][/font_size]\n\nOtwarty sandbox bez punktacji i presji czasu. Dok jest twój.\n\nŁaduj, nawiguj po AS400, wypełniaj dokumenty. Celowo popełniaj błędy — nic nie jest oceniane. Naciśnij [b]Zaplombuj ciężarówkę[/b], aby wrócić do portalu.",
	],

